Race and Inarceration rate

Rona Guo

The evidence of institutional racism and incarceration is painfully obviously when we look at the incarceration rates among different races in the United States. It was and still is a problem that POC, especially Black people, face today.

I decided to focus on the incarceration rate. By comparing the rates, which is the percent of people in jail or prison out of the total population age 15 to 64 of that race, as this age group is the most likely to be incarcerated, for overall population, Black, White, Latinx, and Native people.
